Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.05,0:00:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get the reception attendee list?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.46,0:00:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.72,0:00:12.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got a handle on who was in attendance\Nand where they were at that point in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.18,0:00:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was after the governor?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.14,0:00:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The attendees were all important people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.98,0:00:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd bet most of them have enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.35,0:00:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's keep trying to find any connections\Nthe governor had to the gunman.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.15,0:00:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Frankfurt Station is buzzing\Nwith that convention center shooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.74,0:00:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.57,0:00:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we've identified the deceased attacker...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.99,0:00:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we don't know who he was after.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.66,0:00:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've identified him?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.50,0:00:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.46,0:00:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said he was a dentist from the redevelopment area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.38,0:00:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dentist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.71,0:00:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's just great.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.75,0:00:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was thinking of going to\Na dentist right after I retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.26,0:00:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been to see one because\NI've been so busy every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.89,0:00:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want a dangerous lunatic as my dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.31,0:01:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.86,0:01:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Inspector Weissbach from the\NNordrhein-Westfalen Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.91,0:02:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reinhard Dinger, age forty two.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.45,0:02:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Taxi driver by profession.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.74,0:02:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suspected of killing a passenger in\NGunther Forest Park, as well as...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.37,0:02:50.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the 1997 murder of a Bilker\NInvestment Bank employee...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.59,0:02:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the 1996 Hofgarten murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.84,0:02:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the 1995 Rhine riverside murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.51,0:03:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wanted as a suspect for all these murders that\Noccurred around the D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorf area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.22,0:03:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I now request that the suspect be transferred...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.10,0:03:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the state of Nordrhein-Westfalen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.82,0:03:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you guys ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.53,0:03:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.87,0:03:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Step out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.08,0:03:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:33.27,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(254,100)\pos(362,341)}An Unrelated Murder
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.71,0:03:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want anything to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.01,0:03:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No smoking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.35,0:03:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sign said this is a nonsmoking car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.89,0:03:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you lived with that kind of morality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.23,0:03:56.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many people have you killed with those hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The notion that you can count their\Nprecious lives on your fingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.50,0:04:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would make the people you killed turn in their graves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.97,0:04:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my last case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.14,0:04:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm retiring tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.18,0:04:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I led a simple life\Nas a detective, it wasn't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.02,0:04:34.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'll probably tend the garden\Nwith my wife and take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.36,0:04:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what life is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.69,0:04:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to realize the kind of lives you destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.90,0:04:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I want you to regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.53,0:04:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even people who would spit on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.37,0:04:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man I picked up on Adler Street\Nspit on me when he got off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.42,0:04:57.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me that's why you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.09,0:05:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't spitting on someone the\Nlowest thing a person can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.97,0:05:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two people I picked up at Gerresheim\NStation were even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.02,0:05:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They started having sex in the back of my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.35,0:05:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the back of my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.73,0:05:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I killed them both.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A drunken punk kid with a foul mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.03,0:05:31.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A prostitute who tried to pay her fare with her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.37,0:05:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hag smeared with cosmetics who\Ninsulted everyone she saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.50,0:05:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Many people have ridden in my taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.30,0:05:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.55,0:05:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.68,0:05:52.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the employee from the Bilker\NInvestment Bank that you killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.15,0:05:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was he scum?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.77,0:06:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He worked diligently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.28,0:06:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a good personal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.24,0:06:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a banker who loved his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.20,0:06:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you killed him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.12,0:06:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a certain corporate finance scandal\Nthat he was going to reveal...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:13.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,now remains shrouded in complete mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That one...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.09,0:06:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,left a bad aftertaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.63,0:06:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk as if you're on the moral high ground,\Nbut, you're just trying to justify yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.51,0:06:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have a choice there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.10,0:06:36.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did someone ask you to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.65,0:06:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.53,0:06:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said no smoking in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.42,0:07:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't ever put a cigarette in your\Nmouth in front of me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.80,0:07:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why you turned out this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.60,0:07:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been correct in my thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just needed a little push, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.31,0:07:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.36,0:07:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a man was walking his dog in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.94,0:07:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because the dog took a crap, he kicked it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.41,0:07:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The dog was scared while he was being kicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.24,0:07:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All he did was take a crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.62,0:07:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next thing I knew, the police were holding me down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.06,0:08:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.69,0:08:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a little boy appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it wasn't my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.28,0:08:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That the man walking the dog attacked me first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to that, the police didn't take me away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thanked the boy and offered to\Ndrive him back to his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.80,0:08:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he said he had no home to go back to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.51,0:08:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, he brought his sister\Nfrom the corner of the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.05,0:08:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His twin sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well since I didn't have much choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.56,0:08:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I took them both back to my apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.81,0:08:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The strange thing was, when they started undressing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.15,0:08:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were both wearing pajamas underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.98,0:08:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was as if they had just escaped\Nfrom a hospital or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.95,0:08:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it, the boy had\Na bandage wrapped around his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.95,0:08:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After we ate dinner that night, we watched the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.87,0:09:03.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I started to mutter to myself like I usually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.92,0:09:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a stupid world...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.55,0:09:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What stupid people...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.13,0:09:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trash should just die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the boy said to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.47,0:09:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said that I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.14,0:09:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he said...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:29.23,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,We don t need those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:35.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was liberated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.66,0:09:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.37,0:09:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean to say that that's when you started killing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.63,0:09:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your effort, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.26,0:09:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.68,0:09:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your last case is closed, nice and tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.60,0:10:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. All that's left is to clean out my desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.89,0:10:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much for all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.06,0:10:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel a little depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.27,0:10:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there were a few unsolved cases...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.24,0:10:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.33,0:10:28.17,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,he brought his sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.17,0:10:29.71,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,His twin sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:33.01,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,they were both wearing pajamas...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:35.55,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,as if they had just escaped from a hospital or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.55,0:10:40.68,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember anything about that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.39,0:10:42.81,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.81,0:10:45.14,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.35,0:10:48.35,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Your name is Anna.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.36,0:10:50.15,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Anna Liebert...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:50.98,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.98,0:10:55.74,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that i think about it, the boy had\Na bandage wrapped around his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.49,0:10:58.41,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,The twin brother and sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.41,0:11:00.41,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.66,0:11:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.83,0:11:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When did I meet them?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.13,0:11:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.47,0:11:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About eleven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.63,0:11:20.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What did those children look like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.85,0:11:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were blond twins with very pretty faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.31,0:11:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twins who disappeared that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The twins who hold a vital key to Dr. Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.71,0:11:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.00,0:11:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only have thirty hours until I retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.45,0:12:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A vampire, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.43,0:12:05.77,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(234,200)\pos(356,364)}Isenburg Prison \N (Frankfurt)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.03,0:12:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you sucked the blood of those thirteen people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.91,0:12:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You would have died unless you fed on their blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they had to be virgins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.42,0:12:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.09,0:12:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.30,0:12:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The case from three months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.92,0:12:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The girl from a general store in Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.88,0:12:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frieder Schelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.97,0:12:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you suck her blood as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.85,0:12:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, as you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the people you attacked so far were virgins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.19,0:12:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you even went to the trouble of researching\Ntheir behavior before attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.99,0:12:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why you needed virgin blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, this Frieder Schelling person...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was twenty-one years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.37,0:12:50.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though she looked like she was still in her teens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.54,0:12:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not where the problem lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:13:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She had worked at a caf{\fnMeiryo U}é{\fnNarkisim} on Seiler Street\Nin Frankfurt since she was sixteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.47,0:13:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was very close to a famous school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.39,0:13:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was like a Madonna amongst the boys of that school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.81,0:13:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.56,0:13:13.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she had a child at the age of seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.73,0:13:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the rumors, it was with\Nsomeone from that school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.40,0:13:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After she gave birth, her parents opened a general store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.74,0:13:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stories say that the boy's family was rich...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.16,0:13:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so they received a large sum of money\Nand were able to open the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:33.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.33,0:13:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You conducted extensive research on those other girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.46,0:13:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd even suck the blood of non-virgins?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.05,0:13:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.60,0:13:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,left a bad aftertaste...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you go after her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.69,0:13:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.07,0:13:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.03,0:14:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally realized it after meeting him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.03,0:14:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was only a bat flying around the vampire, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.41,0:14:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.29,0:14:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man asked you to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.67,0:14:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.17,0:14:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Outside of Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.09,0:14:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a park, much like any other park.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.97,0:14:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the sandbox at that park...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he wrote a woman's name in\Nthe sand with a tree branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.19,0:14:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I carried it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.15,0:14:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.36,0:14:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a real vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:48.05,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(351,362)\fad(358)}Pinneber Prison \N (Hamburg)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.28,0:14:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it strange, no matter how you think about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.20,0:14:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your murder of Erich Klemperer four months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All your other missions were in Niedersachsen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.29,0:15:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why was this the only one all the way out in Frankfurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was this another signal from the aliens?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.68,0:15:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the aliens suddenly change their minds\Nand tell you to kill someone in Frankfurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was there another reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.27,0:15:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klemperer certainly did have a sordid history.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.52,0:15:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He escaped from East Berlin during the Cold War.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he was doing well in the trade\Nof food and such for several years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, there were rumors that he\Nsmuggled children over the border.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.08,0:15:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long story short, he was selling eastern children\Nto the rich, childless westerners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.26,0:15:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met one in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.55,0:15:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was inspired.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.18,0:15:55.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A real alien was standing in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.23,0:15:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did the UFO land?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A park in Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.98,0:16:05.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He spoke in a space language.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.99,0:16:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he wrote in the sand...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.74,0:16:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I could understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.29,0:16:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like you to feel the same excitement I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.33,0:16:22.79,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(354,388)}D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorf State Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.05,0:16:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All done here, Inspector Weissbach?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.09,0:16:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're now only seconds away from retiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.77,0:16:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just want me out of here, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.60,0:16:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're going drinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:45.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to celebrate getting rid of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.28,0:16:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like the beer won't taste too good!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.95,0:16:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.29,0:16:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Gillen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:16:59.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear he's a criminal psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.25,0:17:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's here to interview that serial\Nmurderer taxi driver, Dinger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At someone's request?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.67,0:17:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he said if was for his paper or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's got a lot of influence in that domain...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he can convince the higher-ups\Nto give him permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.10,0:17:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, when the man got out\Nof your taxi and spit on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you ran him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.32,0:17:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said the same thing many times during the\Nquestionings, but all the people I killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.49,0:17:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just that you guys can't comprehend my righteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.08,0:17:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Righteousness, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.38,0:17:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've always been very talkative\Nduring the questionings, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.55,0:17:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you seem to have a hard time discussing your\Nmurder of Mr. Overt, the Bilker Bank employee.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:18:02.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's recorded that you claimed your own\Nrighteousness in all your other murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.23,0:18:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you've never given an\Nacceptable reason as to why...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you murdered Mr. Overt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to talk to you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.99,0:18:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go, Dr. Gillen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.37,0:18:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Inspector Weissbach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Dinger confess anything of academic interest to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.67,0:18:30.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing aside from what he's already said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.09,0:18:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.72,0:18:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, there's something I really want to ask him about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.06,0:18:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm retiring today, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.90,0:18:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't feel right unless I hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.40,0:18:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think about this from\Nan academic point of view?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there were a child like a monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.83,0:19:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he grew up and came to visit the man\Nwho fed him in the past, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:09.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A child like a monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.09,0:19:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I know it's a silly story, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.63,0:19:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let me hear more about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.64,0:19:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.27,0:19:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already said I'm not talking to that egghead anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.23,0:19:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still a detective until the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.86,0:19:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an interrogation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.19,0:19:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked you the same thing yesterday,\Nbut about those twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.15,0:19:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said the boy liberated you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that boy grew up and came back to you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.08,0:19:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and asked you to do him a favor...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.17,0:19:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.93,0:20:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.80,0:20:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you murder Fritz Overt who worked\Nat the Bilker Investment Bank...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.02,0:20:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at someone's request?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.90,0:20:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A hard-working guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.73,0:20:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man with a good personal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.74,0:20:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of man Mr. Overt was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.74,0:20:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite different from the trash you so often speak of.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.62,0:20:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was about to reveal a corporate finance scandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.16,0:20:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you call him trash...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then the moralization of your crimes will shatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.51,0:20:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't asked to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.93,0:20:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He and I didn't need to speak to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.27,0:20:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that bank employee was trash to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.73,0:20:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.94,0:20:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.82,0:20:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.78,0:21:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And who was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of those twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.70,0:21:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When and where did you meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.58,0:21:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.49,0:21:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A park in that town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.46,0:21:12.62,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Outside of Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.63,0:21:13.79,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.38,0:21:16.80,Default Italic,,0000,0000,0000,,A park in Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.05,0:21:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wrote a name in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.01,0:21:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was to kill the man with that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't need words.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.52,0:21:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.28,0:21:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that we didn't need a man like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.20,0:21:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.49,0:21:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All three men you interviewed killed someone\Nat the request of the same man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.21,0:21:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By having three completely unrelated\Nserial killers perform the acts...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he made it so that the three murders had no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.96,0:22:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The meaning of the three murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.76,0:22:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.59,0:22:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, be more specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.80,0:22:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both Tenma and Nina headed for Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.52,0:22:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.48,0:22:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.78,0:22:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,trying to do in Frankfurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.84,0:22:31.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,471)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:47.40,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:25.94,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.94,0:23:34.36,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:36.82,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.47,0:23:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
